               <p>THOMAS WILSON. I live in Hoxton Old-town. On the 12th of January, I had just driven my gig up to a stable, facing <placeName id="t18310217-155-crimeloc936">Shoreditch church</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18310217-155-crimeloc936" type="placeName" value="Shoreditch church"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18310217-155-crimeloc936" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310217-155-off934 t18310217-155-crimeloc936"></join>, about half-past eleven o'clock at night; I got out of the gig, had just rung the bell, and on turning round I saw the prisoner take the coat from the side of my gig - he pulled it off, hung it on his arm, and was walking off with it, away from me; I went up to him, and said, "What do you do with that coat, you scoundrel?" the Policeman came, and took him.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. PHILLIPS. Q. What are you? A. A publican; I keep the Plough - I did not perceive that the prisoner was tipsy; he said it was a lark, or something of that kind - he had got about two yards from the gig.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310217-155-person1555">
                  JOHN 
                  MASTERS
               <interp inst="t18310217-155-person1555" type="surname" value="MASTERS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310217-155-person1555" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310217-155-person1555" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was with the prosecutor - I got out of the gig first; I saw the prisoner take the coat - he was walking away with it; he did not appear to be tipsy.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310217-155-person1556">
                  THOMAS 
                  HURRAN
               <interp inst="t18310217-155-person1556" type="surname" value="HURRAN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310217-155-person1556" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310217-155-person1556" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am the officer. I took the prisoner and the coat.</p>

               <p>The prisoner put in a written defence, stating that he was intoxicated; and, in the act of falling down, had caught hold of the coat to save himself, when he was taken.</p>
